DEVELOPER DETAILS
-------------------------

The following information is only relevant to developers.

Techniques Used
-------------------------

- password -l <user> to prevent logins, -u to re-enable
- slay to kill all user processes
- cron.d every minute to perform maintenance and act when necessary
- /var/lib/ file heirarchy for transitory tracker files
- no daemons required for core functionality

System Paths Used
-------------------------

# crontab for tracking
/etc/cron.d/parental-control

# users.d for configuring users
/etc/parental-control/users.d

# example configuration file
/usr/share/parental-control/example.user.conf

# worker scripts
/usr/lib/parental-control

# accounting data
/var/lib/parental-control

# logging
/var/log/parental-control.log
